
NVIDIA
Install CUDA toolkit for windows. (for the OpenCL Lib) http://www.nvidia.com/object/thankyou.html?url=/compute/cuda/3_2_prod/toolkit/cudatoolkit_3.2.16_win_64.msi\

this automatically sets the CUDA_PATH environment variable (used by cmake)
e.g. C:\Program Files\NVIDIA GPU Computing Toolkit\CUDA\v3.2


Download and install Nvidias code samples (this comes prepackaged with glut glew and other utility libraries) http://developer.download.nvidia.com/compute/cuda/3_2_prod/sdk/gpucomputingsdk_3.2.16_win_64.exe
This automatically sets the NVSDKCOMPUTE_ROOT variable (used by cmake
e.g. C:\ProgramData\NVIDIA Corporation\NVIDIA GPU Computing SDK 3.2



#Download and install visual studio 10 express edition.
#http://go.microsoft.com/?linkid=9709949
Download and install visual studio 8 express edition
http://www.microsoft.com/express/Downloads/#2008-Visual-CPP

Download Windows SDK
http://www.microsoft.com/downloads/dlx/en-us/listdetailsview.aspx?FamilyID=6b6c21d2-2006-4afa-9702-529fa782d63b


Download git/cmake for windows.

clone enjaparticles from git terminal
    create a build directory
    run cmake
    point source directory to rtps
    point build directory to your build directory
    press configure
    press generate
    navigate to build directory
    double-click on rtpssuite.sln
    when visual studio opens.
    right-click on sph.x in the left panel and select build
    right-click INSTALL in the left panel and select build
    check in the build/bin directory and execute sph.x


Compiling blender
http://wiki.blender.org/index.php/Dev:2.5/Doc/Building_Blender/Windows/msvc/CMake


    cd ..
    mkdir build25rtps
    run cmake
    point source directory to BGERTPS/blender
    point build directory to your build25rtps directory
    press configure
    press generate

    navigate to build directory
    double-click on Blender.sln
    when visual studio opens.
        right-click INSTALL in the left panel and select build
    
    check in the build/bin directory and execute blender.exe





